{
  "stem": "25639.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they turned it over to a-- an individual who was a male, and who was a member of the underground.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And these people, these men, were part of the sonderkommando.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The sonderkommando is a German term for a group of men who did nothing but took care of the bodies once they were gassed.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They-- once these people were gassed, they had to take the bodies out on wheelbarrow type of vehicles, and they-- they took them into the crematorium and burned the bodies there.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so the-- the-- the death process is what they were assigned to do.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It's that or die.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "One day, the sonderkommando-- and I would really prefer to call them the underground in this case, for there may have been others involved, and I-- I don't know-- blew up gas chamber and crematorium number four.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And a few days later, the-- the news reached us by way of the grapevine that the reason we no longer can work in gas chamber and crematorium number four is because it was blown up and put out of action.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Thousands and thousands of men, women, and children were able to save their lives as a result of this action.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We-- we were jubilant.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We were jubilant, and why couldn't this be done before and-- and elsewhere, hopefully, if-- we-- actually, when we were in Auschwitz, we had no idea that there were other camps until there were others who were transferred into our camp.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then we learned that this one came from this camp, and that one came from that, and so forth and so on.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we said, yet another camp?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe four or five or six camps?",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
